      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for that. but wait, i think the ratios you gave for the perfect fifth might be wrong? i thought a perfect fifth was more like 3:2. can u explain the mechanics of the \"interference\" part more? like, what is actually happening physically with the sound waves when they are that close together that makes it feel so grating or \"unpleasant\" to the listener?",
      "source": "evaluator"
