      "content": "The discomfort or tension associated with dissonant sounds can be described as a result of the(plane-wave) interference pattern between the two frequencies, which creates a perceived sense of \"high-amplitude\" or \"narrow-band\" noise. This type of noise triggers the brain's alertness response, releasing cortisol and adrenaline, and activating the brain's perception of warning or danger. Research has also shown that discordant sounds can activate the insula, a region of the brain associated with emotion, sensory processing, and interoception. This activation can lead to feelings of discomfort, tension, or unease in the listener.",
